# Precision Weapons & Reloading Context

You are working on the precision weapons or reloading stack that supports the contract sandbox. Read these docs:

1. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` — shared patterns
2. `docs/design/reloading-system.md` — reloading data models, process steps, equipment
3. `docs/design/weapons-and-ballistics.md` — weapon parts, ballistics model, shooting
4. `docs/design/weapon-view-attachment-runtime.md` — required runtime contract for weapon view prefabs and attachment mounting when touching first-person weapon views or attachments
5. `docs/design/assassination-contracts.md` — load only when the change affects contract execution, long-range jobs, or target-prep flow
6. `.agent/skills/reloading-domain-knowledge/SKILL.md` — accuracy calculation, real-world reference (only if implementing accuracy/ballistics)
7. `.agent/skills/adding-game-content/SKILL.md` — only when creating/editing ScriptableObject data assets under `Reloader/Assets/_Project/Reloading/Data/**` or `Reloader/Assets/_Project/Weapons/Data/**`
8. `.agent/skills/weapon-view-attachment-framework/SKILL.md` — required when changing weapon view prefabs, attachment slots, attachment runtime, or view/scene wiring for weapons

For logic/bugfix/refactor tasks in scripts, skip `adding-game-content`.

Do NOT load unrelated deep-domain docs unless the task explicitly crosses boundaries.
